title: Bob and Ray, Jane Laraine and Gilda.avi
description:
This great one-off starred the women of "Classic" SNL: Jane Curtin, Laraine Newman and Gilda Radner along with the great comedy duo Bob & Ray performing some sketch versions of their material as well as some new stuff. It's kind of a meeting of two comedy generations. Released on video ages ago, it has yet to make it to DVD or the internet until now (as far as I have been able to make out).

Video is just over an hour, scanned hi-res from a first-generation tape. Special musical guest is Willie Nelson.

Highlights:
* B&R do their version of "Do Ya Think I'm Sexy?" with the girls
* Willie Nelson and Leon Russell perform "One For My Baby"
* The non-identical McBeeBee twins, a longstanding B&R favorite.

Video: 1:08:10
Res: 720x480
Compression: XVid 2000kbps video, mp3 128kbps audio
